 said `` it would appear ... Mr. <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Kooning </PERSON> suffers from Alzheimer's disease,'' the magazine said. Alzheimer's disease is a progressive, irreversible disorder whose symptoms include gradual memory loss, impairment of judgment, disorientation, personality change, difficulty in learning and loss of language skills. The petition said Ms. <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Kooning </PERSON> is the sole beneficiary of her father's will and last year received about $ 25,000 a month from him, according to ARTnews. Ms. <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Kooning </PERSON>, an animal rights activist and amateur sculptor who is married and has a child, has lived in a house her father built for her on his property since 1983. No date has been set for a hearing on the petition, according to ARTnews. Court officials were not available for comment Sunday. If granted, the petition would give Ms. <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Kooning </PERSON> and Eastman control over the artist's representation and his assets, which include $ 7 million in real estate, cash and securities and more than 300 paintings. The average worth of each painting is estimated to be between $ 300,000 and $ 650,000. However, his `` Pink Lady'' sold at a 1988 <ORGANIZATION> Sotheby </ORGANIZATION>'s auction for $ 3.6 million.
