<HEAD>Opposition Party Formed, Laurel At Head, Urges Marcos Return</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By CLARO CORTES</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A revived opposition party urged President <PERSON> Corazon </PERSON> <PERSON> Aquino </PERSON> Sunday to call new elections, and the group's new secretary-general said the president should allow <PERSON> Ferdinand </PERSON> <PERSON> Marcos </PERSON> to return as a sign of her leadership. The call came at the end of a one-day convention of the <ORGANIZATION> Nationalista </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>. The 4,000 delegates agreed to revive the party as the major opposition movement against Mrs. <PERSON> Aquino </PERSON>. Vice President <PERSON> Salvador </PERSON> <PERSON> Laurel </PERSON> was named party president, Sen. <PERSON> Juan </PERSON> <PERSON> Ponce </PERSON> <PERSON> Enrile </PERSON> was designated secretary-general and <PERSON> Blas </PERSON> <PERSON> Ople </PERSON>, a labor minister under <PERSON> Marcos </PERSON>, was chosen executive vice president, both by acclamation. Laurel quit as foreign secretary on September 1987 and refused to serve in the Cabinet, claiming `` fundamental differences'' with Mrs. <PERSON> Aquino </PERSON>. <PERSON> Laurel </PERSON> remains as vice president, which is an elective post. During the convention, <PERSON> Enrile </PERSON>, a former defense minister, said Mrs. <PERSON> Aquino </PERSON> should display leadership by allowing <PERSON> Marcos </PERSON> to return from <LOCATION> Hawaii </LOCATION> to die in his homeland. `` We believe that <PERSON> Marcos </PERSON> should be allowed to come back,'' <PERSON> Enrile </PERSON> said. `` There is no reason why he should be deprived of his right to come home at this time of his life. He's so ill. How can he destabilize the country? The former president was reported in critical condition Sunday in a <LOCATION> Honolulu </LOCATION> hospital after undergoing emergency kidney surgery. Hospital officials said his prognosis is poor, although he showed signs of responding to treatment. On Friday, Mrs. <PERSON> Aquino </PERSON> refused to allow <PERSON> Marcos </PER