<HEAD>Train Collides with Auto, Killing Driver; 40 Cars Derailed</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Restores overline, recasts lead to tighten</HEAD>
<DATELINE>QUINCY, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A freight train collided with an automobile at a grade crossing early Sunday, killing the driver and causing 40 cars to derail, state police said. The 21-year-old automobile driver was killed when he apparently tried to out-run the 72-car <ORGANIZATION> Burlington </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Northern </ORGANIZATION> freight train at the crossing northeast of Quincy, said Trooper <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Kastel </PERSON>. One train crewman was treated for minor injuries. The dead man, a resident of <PERSON> Quincy </PERSON>, was not identified pending notification of his relatives. He was alone in the car. There was no threat from any hazardous materials and no fire in the derailment, <PERSON> Kastel </PERSON> said. The damage was estimated to be to be over $ 1.25 million. <LOCATION> Burlington </LOCATION> Northern officials were not immediately available for comment.
