<HEAD>Say Alfonsin and Menen Consider Early Transfer of Power</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS with 5 grafs to UPDATE with Alfonsin agreement to move
up inauguration; pickup 5th graf, `Menem, the ...'</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By ED McCULLOUGH</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BUENOS AIRES, Argentina (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 President <PERSON> Raul </PERSON> <PERSON> Alfonsin </PERSON> agreed Sunday to move up the scheduled Dec. 10 inauguration of President-elect <PERSON> Carlos </PERSON> <PERSON> Menem </PERSON> because of <LOCATION> Argentina </LOCATION>'s economic crisis. But <PERSON> Alfonsin </PERSON>, in a statement, said no date was set after he and <PERSON> Menem </PERSON> held a daylong meeting with aides. The <ORGANIZATION> Central </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> meanwhile ordered all banks and foreign exchange houses closed Monday while the government prepared a new economic plan that will include price controls and export taxes. `` I have said and I repeat, I am not going to flee any responsibility,'' <PERSON> Alfonsin </PERSON> said late Sunday in a statement read to reporters by press secretary <PERSON> Jose </PERSON> <PERSON> Ignacio </PERSON> <PERSON> Lopez </PERSON>. `` Nevertheless, I note that in the context of a severe economic crisis, the period of transition is too long,'' <PERSON> Alfonsin </PERSON> said after meeting with his Cabinet. <PERSON> Menem </PERSON>, the <ORGANIZATION> Peronist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> leader who won the May 14 presidential election, told the newspaper <PERSON> Clarin </PERSON> in an interview published Sunday that he would take office early `` if there is a general consensus of our entire community.'' He said that would include business, labor and political groups, the armed forces and leaders of the the Roman Catholic church. In the elections earlier this month the Peronists also won virtual contol of both houses of <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Alfonsin </PERSON>'s inauguration in December 1983, following elections that October, ended nearly eight years of military dictatorships. He was barred by the constitution from seeking a second term. <PERSON> Menem </PERSON> defeated <PERSON> Eduardo </PERSON> <PERSON> Angeloz </PERSON>, the <ORGANIZATION> Radical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Civic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION> candidate. Sources in both parties, speaking with the condition they not be identified, said discussions were being held on how to move up <PERSON> Menem </PERSON>'s inauguration without violating the constitution and if the new <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> also should be sworn in early. Peronist Congressman <PERSON> Eduardo </PERSON> <PERSON> Bauza </PERSON> said Sunday his party is demanding that <PERSON> Alfonsin </PERSON>'s economic team resign. `` They are in great measure responsible for this crisis,'' he said. <PERSON> Bauza </PERSON> also said the transfer of power could be held July 9, <LOCATION> Argentina </LOCATION>'s independence day. <PERSON> Bauza </PERSON> is considered to be a contender for finance minister in a Peronist administration. The economic situation is putting pressure on both parties. Interest has not been paid since last year on the country's $ 59 billion foreign debt. <PERSON> Menem </PERSON> has said the <ORGANIZATION> Central </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> has only $ 300 million in reserves. Economists say the banking system is in jeopardy. They say about $ 170 million in bonds fall due this week and banks could have trouble raising the money.
